<span id="freeTextContainer7603426286455808161">☺️☺️☺️☺️<br/><br/>This was really lovely. It was perfectly written (seriously, Gabrielle Zevin has mastered using the English language), and heartfelt. It was a little sappy at times, but it felt appropriate. I loved the span of this book - over a decade of fascinating stuff happened. And I loved the setting - a book store on a tiny island. I loved the emphasis on books and love and trying to be a good person. <br/><br/>I&apos;m not giving a 5/5 simply because I don&apos;t think it did anything particularly new, and didn&apos;t m</span>
  <span id="freeText7603426286455808161" style="display:none">☺️☺️☺️☺️<br /><br />This was really lovely. It was perfectly written (seriously, Gabrielle Zevin has mastered using the English language), and heartfelt. It was a little sappy at times, but it felt appropriate. I loved the span of this book - over a decade of fascinating stuff happened. And I loved the setting - a book store on a tiny island. I loved the emphasis on books and love and trying to be a good person. <br /><br />I'm not giving a 5/5 simply because I don't think it did anything particularly new, and didn't make me think about something I'd never thought about before. That's okay, and it doesn't make this book in anyway bad, but it didn't leave me blown away and so four stars it is.</span>
